1️⃣ How a Web Server Works (Flow)
Basic Flow
User opens browser.
User enters URL → http://example.com/home
Browser sends HTTP Request to server.
Web Server receives request.
Server processes request using backend code.
Server sends HTTP Response (HTML/JSON).
Browser renders page.

-------------------------------------------------------

Request–Response Cycle
Client → Request → Server
Server → Response → Client

-------------------------------------------------------

Components
Client → Browser (Chrome, Edge)
Web Server → Tomcat / Jetty
Application → Spring Boot App
Database → MySQL/PostgreSQL (optional)

-------------------------------------------------------

HTTP Methods
GET → Fetch data
POST → Send data
PUT → Update data
DELETE → Delete data
